JOHANNESBURG - Police discovered piles of arms and explosives at a building that is being renovated in the Randburg CBD on Monday.Police spokesman Mavela Masondo said bomb and dog units discovered mortar bombs, hand grenades, rifles, pistols and revolvers in a basement room.The police were called to the premises after workmen renovating the building found a suspicious bag.It was found to contain explosives.Masondo there was also a suicide vest among the ammunition and weapons, which included R5 and AK-47 rifles.He said it had not yet been ascertained how long the cache might have been there, but it appeared to have been some time as there was some rust on a few weapons.The police would track down the previous owner of the recently sold building as part of their investigation, he said.The weapons found were the kind typically used in armed robberies, he said.eNCA